¬Microsoft has pioneered reference architecture frameworks for industries such as upstream oil and gas operations (MURA), smart energy and water (SERA), discrete manufacturing (DIRA) and chemical and oil refining (ChemRA).  They are Industry-validated and provide guidance on addressing technology challenges and developments. SERA provides an end-to-end reference architecture for an integrated utilities company.

¬Microsoft platforms incorporate an advanced security model for controlling access to data.  'Role based' privileges ensure users can only perform actions relevant to them.  With access so easily controlled, it's easy to segment responsibilities for analysing and extracting insights from data, across many different industry scenarios and including your partner organisations.

Large amounts of data can provide very powerful insights but these are only useful when everyone is using the same, correct, base data. Microsoft can help to ensure all insight is being driven from a single, agreed source or set of sources, allowing you to have complete confidence in the insight gained.

With Power BI for Office 365 you can query data using natural language and see almost-instantaneous results in the form of interactive visualisations. The Q&A feature, guides users on questions to ensure answers match the question intent.  Best practices can also improve the quality of the answers.
